<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1609">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/61.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-24">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Exert every possible influence to prevent hostile action against
                                Chinese or any other foreigners. Ask Carranza to furnish necessary
                                force to restrain mob. Give asylum to any foreigners whose lives are
                                in danger. If necessary conduct them to American side and hold them
                                and care for them until you receive further instructions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>